    <h1 class="xar-mod-head">
        <xar:mlstring>jQuery demo page</xar:mlstring>
    </h1>

    <p><xar:mlstring>Note: the Xaraya_Classic theme causes most of these plugins to fail one way or another.
    We don't know where the fault lies, but it is something to bear in mind when trying this demo out.</xar:mlstring></p>

    <h2><xar:mlstring>Calendar - jquery-calendar</xar:mlstring></h2>

    <p><xar:mlstring>Basic calendar pop-up</xar:mlstring></p>

    <xar:template file="jquery-calendar" module="jquery" subdata="array('selector'=&gt;'#jquery-calendar-item')" />

    <form><input type="text" id="jquery-calendar-item" /></form>

    <h2><xar:mlstring>Calendar - datePicker</xar:mlstring></h2>

    <p><xar:mlstring>Advanced calendar, supporting i18n formats, defaults, linked 'range' dates, plus lots of other options.</xar:mlstring></p>

    <xar:template file="jquery.datePicker" module="jquery" subdata="array('selector'=&gt;'#datePickerItem')" />

    <form><input type="text" id="datePickerItem" /></form>

    <xar:comment>The datePicker seems to use a float that needs to be cleared</xar:comment>
    <div style="clear: both;"></div>

